The paper deals with linear inverse problems, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), and Signal Processing (cs.SP) communities. The focus on sparsity and low-rank assumptions also suggests these categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the existence of an orthonormal basis, which is a topic in Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and considers structured sparsity and sparse inverse covariance matrices, which are topics in Statistics (cs.SI).
